Project3

Class Queue

  • java.lang.Object
    • Project3.Queue

  • public class Queue
extends java.lang.Object
    Create a class named Queue that implements a queue (double-ended queue, actually) of state objects using a doubly linked list. Support the following methods:

    [Queue()]a.Constructor that creates the queue.

    [insertEnd(State)]b.An insertEnd method to insert a state at the end of the queue.

    [insertFront(State)]c.An insertFront method to insert a state at the front of the queue.

    [removeEnd()]d.A removeEnd method to remove a state from the end of the queue and return it.

    [removeFront()]e.A removeFront method to remove a state from the front of the queue and return it.

    [findDelete(String)]f.A findDelete method to find a state in the queue by state name, and delete it from the queue. Return true if it was found and deleted and false otherwise.

    [printQueue()]g.A printQueue method to print the queue in order front to end

    [isEmpty()]h.An isEmpty method that returns true if the queue is empty, false otherwise

    [isFull()]i.An isFull method that returns false always

    Version:
    10/28/2017
    Author:
    Ryan Geddings N01067534
